sentences: Karen Brooks (born April 30, 1954) is an American country music singer and songwriter who is best known for a series of singles recorded by Emmylou Harris, Rosanne Cash, Patty Loveless, Tanya Tucker, Russell Smith, David Allen Coe, Crystal Gayle and Exile.
She sang a duet with Johnny Cash, "I Will Dance With You", and  also with T. G. Sheppard, "Faking Love", which was a number one hit on the Billboard country chart in February 1983.
She attended Justin F. Kimball High School with schoolmate Stevie Ray Vaughan (Class of '72).
